{"questionId":"22316845","questionHtml":"<p>Using the definitions of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>∙</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi></mfenced></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>∙</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math> be the angle between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></math>.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">·</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">u</mi><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-ital